# Code owners. Combined with branch protection ("Require review from Code
# Owners"), these paths can't merge without @tomfuertes approval.
#
# The .claude/ and .github/ entries are a supply-chain control, not just review
# routing: this is a forkable template, and the config-injection vector is a PR
# that slips a malicious SessionStart hook into .claude/settings.json or a
# poisoned workflow into .github/. Gating those paths closes it.

# Default owner for everything not matched below.
*                       @tomfuertes

# Agent/editor config — config-injection surface.
/.claude/               @tomfuertes

# CI, automation, and dependency policy.
/.github/               @tomfuertes

# Deploy-critical: a bad edit here crash-loops the Railway container.
/Dockerfile             @tomfuertes
/start.sh               @tomfuertes
/railway.toml           @tomfuertes
